channel.title: IP Address not working correctly
channel.description:
[b]I've been testing random sources out and my friend as been helping me, but all of a sudden two sources in a row will not let me login, and I have not reset my router and I've like triple checked my port forwarding but still no luck.
[u]First Source [/u] Changed one IP in Gui.java Changed two to three IP's in client.java
[u]Second Source[/u] Changed three IP's in Client.java
Both are Project Insanity based.
Wondering is it something in the server files. (I don't think so.)[/b]

In pi you don’t have to change the ip in the source files, just go to the client files and go to client.java and search "server = " and change that to the ip your server is running on.
